<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="video_games"><strong>Video games and consoles</strong></h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>1. Xbox Series X and Xbox Series S</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png"><img decoding="async" width="1090" height="610" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png" alt="Xbox Series X Christmas gift guide" class="wp-image-99269" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png 1090w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=310,173 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=768,430 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=1024,573 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=620,347 620w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=360,201 360w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=720,403 720w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=400,224 400w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/Xbox-Series-X.png?resize=800,448 800w" sizes="(max-width: 1090px) 100vw, 1090px" /></a></figure>



<p>One of the two titans of console gaming in the 2020s, the latest Xbox models possess top-line graphics and ridiculously quick processing power. For the ultimate experience, you need the Series X, which comes with a large 1Tb hard drive and a slot for games discs – this is retro-compatible with titles from older Xbox consoles, so your library of games amassed over the years doesn’t need to be declared obsolete.</p>



<p>If you need something a little cheaper, the entry Series S has a smaller hard drive (512Gb) and slightly detuned hardware, plus it doesn’t come with a disc drive, but it’s still capable of running some of the best games available for the Microsoft platform. There’s also now a 1Tb Xbox Series S if you need more storage space for games.</p>



<p><strong>Xbox Series X price:</strong> £429-£459.99<br><strong>Buy it at</strong> <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.argos.co.uk%2Fproduct%2F8448262%3FclickPR%3Dplp%3A1%3A1" target="_blank">Argos</a>, <a href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.currys.co.uk%2Fproducts%2Fmicrosoft-xbox-series-x-1-tb-10203371.html">Currys</a> or <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.game.co.uk%2Fen%2Fxbox%2Fconsoles%2Fxbox-series-x%2F%3Fcm_sp%3DXboxFormatHub-_-Consoles-_-Espot1-XSX" target="_blank">Game</a></p>



<p><strong>Xbox Series S price: </strong>£249<br><strong>Buy it at</strong> <a href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.argos.co.uk%2Fproduct%2F8448248%3FclickSR%3Dslp%3Aterm%3Axbox%2520series%2520s%3A1%3A344%3A1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Argos</a>, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.currys.co.uk/products/microsoft-xbox-series-s-512-gb-ssd-10205195.html" target="_blank">Currys</a> or <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.game.co.uk%2Fen%2Fxbox%2Fconsoles%2Fxbox-series-s%2F%3Fcm_sp%3DXboxFormatHub-_-Consoles-_-Espot2-XSS" target="_blank">Game</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2. PlayStation 5</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1152" height="644" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png" alt="PS5 Christmas Gift Guide" class="wp-image-99270" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png 1152w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=310,173 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=768,429 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=1024,572 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=620,347 620w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=360,201 360w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=720,403 720w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=400,224 400w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2019/11/PS5-2-e1605037819512.png?resize=800,447 800w" sizes="(max-width: 1152px) 100vw, 1152px" /></figure>



<p>Sony released its latest generation games console, the PS5, in 2020. For car enthusiasts, the big title for PS5 is <em>Gran Turismo 7</em>, the legendary Sony-exclusive racing game launched in early 2022, with rallying sims such as the <em>Dirt</em> series also good fun. </p>



<p>Like the Xbox Series X, the PS5 packs a punch with an ultra-high-speed hard drive, 4K graphics, 8K HDR, 120 fps and ray tracing. It also looks pretty cool compared to the Xbox’s cube-like design, though be warned it’s a fair bit larger than the PS4, so takes up more room on the shelf.</p>



<p>The PS5 is available in two forms — the standard model or a cheaper Digital version, which has the same performance but comes without the disc drive. It’s backwards compatible so if you want to run your old PS4 discs on the PS5, best opt for the pricier model.</p>



