</figure>



<p>This company offers a delightful selection of various car-themed posters that are sure to wow the petrolhead in your life. There are various sizes and finishes available, with wide-ranging subject matters to boot. So, for example, you can pick the evolution of the Porsche 911 GT3 through the years, or some of the most iconic film cars over the decades, or your favourite GP circuits, or even old car adverts and portraits of motorsport greats. </p>



<p>There’s also the ability to send in a picture of a personal vehicle and have Rear View Prints turn it into a poster — perfect if the car-lover in your family wants something more bespoke to their particular dream set of wheels.</p>



<p><strong>Price</strong> £19.99 to £199.99<br><strong>Buy it at</strong> <a href="https://rearviewprints.com/category/all-posters/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">RearViewPrints.com</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>3. Boring Car Trivia books by Richard Porter</strong></h3>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img decoding="async" width="626" height="500" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?w=626" alt="Boring car trivia 3 book by Richard Porter - Christmas gift ideas for car lovers" class="wp-image-109062" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg 626w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?resize=310,248 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?resize=483,386 483w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?resize=280,224 280w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?resize=561,448 561w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?resize=312,249 312w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2021/11/Boring-car-triva.jpg?resize=623,498 623w" sizes="(max-width: 626px) 100vw, 626px" /></figure></div>


<p>If you’re a fan — or someone in your life is — of painfully dull automotive minutiae, Richard Porter’s brilliant Boring Car Trivia Books are well worth a look.</p>



<p>So popular was Porter’s Medium-Sized Book of Boring Car Trivia, that he followed it up with two more volumes, respectively titled Boring Car Trivia Volume 2 and Boring Car Trivia 3. The hilarious script editor of The Grand Tour (a.k.a. Sniff Petrol), revels in the most tedious automotive facts that are sure to delight and thrill hardcore car enthusiasts and, as the titles suggest, thoroughly bore everyone else.</p>



<p>Rather than just being a list of facts, all three books are written with good humour and an eye for the absurd. Given that there are three of them (all reasonably priced) they make for either a riveting trio or, as single volumes, nice small gifts. Look out for the fourth in the series, which is coming soon.</p>



<ul>
<li>A Medium-Sized Book of Boring Car Trivia, £4.50 from Amazon – <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Medium-sized-Book-Boring-Car-Trivia/dp/B087646CX6/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2L77AND9BYXZJ&amp;keywords=richard+porter+car+trivia&amp;qid=1651673746&amp;sprefix=car+trivia+richar,aps,195&amp;sr=8-1#_blank" target="_blank">buy here</a></li>



<li>Boring Car Trivia Volume 2, £4.99 from Amazon – <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Boring-Car-Trivia-Sniff-Petrol/dp/B08NZTXM46/ref=sr_1_3?crid=2L77AND9BYXZJ&amp;keywords=richard+porter+car+trivia&amp;qid=1651674324&amp;sprefix=car+trivia+richar,aps,195&amp;sr=8-3#_blank" target="_blank">buy here</a></li>



<li>Boring Car Trivia 3, £4.99 from Amazon – <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Boring-Car-Trivia-Sniff-Petrol/dp/B09K1FHLYH/ref=sr_1_2?crid=2L77AND9BYXZJ&amp;keywords=richard+porter+car+trivia&amp;qid=1651674412&amp;sprefix=car+trivia+richar,aps,195&amp;sr=8-2#_blank" target="_blank">buy here</a></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>4. Enzo Ferrari: The Man and the Machine by Brock Yates</strong></h3>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="326" height="500" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png" alt="" class="wp-image-137005" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png 326w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png?resize=202,310 202w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png?resize=252,386 252w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png?resize=146,224 146w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png?resize=292,448 292w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png?resize=162,249 162w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-11.png?resize=325,498 325w" sizes="(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px" /></figure></div>


<p>With the biopic of “old man” Enzo Ferrari — starring Adam Driver, who played Kylo Ren in the Star Wars sequels — coming out just after Christmas, you can get your car-fanatical relations ahead of the curve with this in-depth look into the life of the famous Italian. </p>



<p>The book by American journalist Brock Yates delves into the behind-the-scenes persona of Ferrari, a man who was known for a combative management style and various controversies in his life, so this book should be a fascinating, rollercoaster read about the formation of this world-renowned automotive marque.</p>



<p><strong>Price </strong>£12.99<br><strong>Buy it at </strong><a href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.waterstones.com%2Fbook%2Fenzo-ferrari%2Fenzo-ferrari-brock-yates%2F9780241977163" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Waterstones.com</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>5. Gran Turismo movie</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1280" height="1653" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?w=793" alt="" class="wp-image-137006" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png 1280w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=240,310 240w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=768,992 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=793,1024 793w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=1189,1536 1189w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=299,386 299w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=173,224 173w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=347,448 347w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=193,249 193w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-12.png?resize=386,498 386w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></figure>



<p>No, we’ve not gone mad and listed the game twice — this is the film, based on the true story of Jann Mardenborough, a young gamer who was a dab hand at the <em>Gran Turismo </em>PlayStation series. He then won the third iteration of the GT Academy in 2011, an annual competition to transform gamers into proper racing drivers — and he’s been a professional motorsport combatant since. </p>



<p>OK, so the film based on his life isn’t going to be a cerebral experience like watching a mind-bending Christopher Nolan flick, but it promises to be a few hours of solid crash-bang-wallop racing entertainment. In his review for Driving.co.uk, Will Dron said: &#8220;it’s very obviously a marketing movie at times &#8230; but there is real heart within the true story&#8221;, and he noted the stellar cast.</p>



<p>And yes, we know people stream films nowadays, but you can hardly wrap up a subscription to Netflix and pop it under the Christmas tree like you can a nice 4K Blu-ray disc, right?</p>



<p><strong>Price </strong>£24.99 (Blu-ray 4K)<br><strong>Buy it at </strong><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fhmv.com%2Fstore%2Ffilm-tv%2F4k-ultra-hd-blu-ray%2Fgran-turismo%3Fgad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQiAr8eqBhD3ARIsAIe-buNCTP6hYeBsrrDWqrP94MhWL6mVrgGjlkBFA4O_Q1JRrxWTZG_zvqgaAlmBEALw_wcB%26gclsrc%3Daw.ds" target="_blank">HMV.co</a><a href="https://go.skimresources.com?id=34784X1557322&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fhmv.com%2Fstore%2Ffilm-tv%2F4k-ultra-hd-blu-ray%2Fgran-turismo%3Fgad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQiAr8eqBhD3ARIsAIe-buNCTP6hYeBsrrDWqrP94MhWL6mVrgGjlkBFA4O_Q1JRrxWTZG_zvqgaAlmBEALw_wcB%26gclsrc%3Daw.ds" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">m</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>6. Bond Cars: The Definitive History &#8211; Jason Barlow</strong></h3>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="392" height="500" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png" alt="" class="wp-image-137007" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png 392w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png?resize=243,310 243w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png?resize=303,386 303w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png?resize=176,224 176w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png?resize=351,448 351w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png?resize=195,249 195w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/image-13.png?resize=390,498 390w" sizes="(max-width: 392px) 100vw, 392px" /></figure></div>


<p>If you want to guarantee a nice, heated debate in the post-Christmas-dinner lull on December 25, then get people talking about which is the best Bond car in history. Jason Barlow, a motoring journalist and former <em>Top Gear</em> presenter, does the groundwork for you with this thorough look back at every significant car that has appeared on screen in the venerable spy film franchise. </p>



<p>So to arm someone with the right knowledge to win that Christmas Bond car argument, this is the book to provide all the information needed. </p>



<p>But just so you know, it’s definitely the Lotus Esprit S1 from <em>The Spy Who Loved Me</em>.  </p>



<p><strong>Price </strong>£30 (hardback)<br><strong>Buy it at </strong><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.waterstones.com/book/bond-cars/jason-barlow/9781785945144" target="_blank">Waterstones.com</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>7. Limited100 automotive artworks</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="5183" height="3373" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-137059" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg 5183w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=310,202 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=768,500 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=1024,666 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=1536,1000 1536w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=2048,1333 2048w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=593,386 593w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=344,224 344w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=688,448 688w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=383,249 383w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/will-dron-limited100-pic.jpg?resize=765,498 765w" sizes="(max-width: 5183px) 100vw, 5183px" /></figure>



<p>Nottingham-based Limited100 sells art prints from a curated group of photographers, with printing and framing completed by the in-house specialists over as much as six hours per order. Each print is part of a limited run of no more than 100 , ensuring a certain amount of exclusivity, too. </p>



<p><strong>Price </strong>From £119 to £589; supersize acrylic glass from £5,899; photoshoot and print package £1,089<br><strong>Buy it at</strong> <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.limited100.co.uk/" target="_blank">Limited100.co.uk</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>8. <strong>75 Years of Motorsport at Goodwood</strong> book</strong> </h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1000" height="1200" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?w=853" alt="" class="wp-image-137110" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg 1000w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=258,310 258w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=768,922 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=853,1024 853w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=322,386 322w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=187,224 187w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=373,448 373w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=208,249 208w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/11/0001779_2.jpg?resize=415,498 415w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></figure>



<p>This beautiful hardback coffee-table book does what it says on the cover — it begins with the first event in 1948 at the Goodwood Motor Circuit, while also documenting the original Festival of Speed in 1993 and the inaugural Revival of 1998, bringing the reader right up to the present day, celebrating 75 years of motor sport activity at Goodwood.</p>



<p>A selection of carefully curated photos and stories are told across 336 glossy pages, covering all kinds of motor sport disciplines, as well as championing the tales of both the machines and the drivers which have made headlines at the Sussex circuit over the years. Priced at a pound for every year covered in the book; neat.</p>



<p><strong>Price </strong>£75<br><strong>Buy it at</strong> <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://shop.goodwood.com/products/book-gw-75yrs-of-motorsport" target="_blank">Goodwood.com</a></p>



